# development moved to arcticdb github repository

this repository and project are now in maintenance mode. development has migrated to [arcticdb](https://github.com/man-group/arcticdb).

---

information on how to set up, install and use arctic has been moved to [readme-arctic.md](readme-arctic.md).

documentation_summary: The HTML text describes the GitHub repository "man-group/arctic," a high-performance datastore designed for time series and tick data. The repository has garnered attention with 3,000 stars and 582 forks, indicating its popularity and utility within the community. It is licensed under LGPL-2.1 and has been developed primarily in Python. The project has now moved to maintenance mode, with development shifting to ArcticDB. The repository includes various resources such as documentation, issues, pull requests, and discussions for contributors and users. Additionally, it provides links to setup and installation instructions, emphasizing its focus on time series databases and its application in fields requiring efficient data storage solutions.
